column1: For every Emergency Department encounter, hospitals may report a Principal Procedure and up to 20 Other Procedures.  The Procedure Code Frequency Report shows the frequency, in each position, of the reporting of each code.
Procedure Code = the procedure code, according to CPT-4 (Current Procedural Terminology, Fourth Edition).
TotalProc = the total number of times the procedure code was reported in a Principal or Other Procedure position.
pr0 = the total number of times the procedure code was reported as a Principal Procedure.
pr1-pr24 = the total number of times the procedure code was reported in each Other Procedure position.
Data Source: California Emergency Department Database, Office of Statewide Health Planning and Development
